WeSwap

Objectives:
Through its WeSwap app the platform stimulates waste reduction by allowing people to give away or reuse items without purchasing new products.
Through its circular economy approach the app lowers environmental emissions from the manufacturing process along with shipping activities and landfill disposal of waste. 
WeSwap builds systems to foster eco-friendly actions amongst people and communities through programs that enhance sustainability availability and encourage participation.

SDGs Targeted: 
SDG 13: Through its features the app operates as a climate action solution by lowering industrials pollution levels while reducing demand for products and helping users adopt environment-friendly habits.
SDG 12: Through its support of item reuse and upcycling the platform promotes responsible consumer practices that diminish waste output.
SDG 11: Local meetup spaces and drop-off zones found within the app help develop community-driven sustainability projects to make cities more environmentally conscious.
SDG 17: The app functions with NGOs and eco-friendly businesses and government programs through Partnerships for the Goals initiatives to support expanded sustainability outcomes and integrative sustainable practices.


Features:
1. Users on this platform utilize their unused items to trade swaps and donate to both charitable non-profits and local organizations.
2. The platform helps decrease product waste and maintains product lifecycles.
3. The platform calculates estimated carbon reductions from swapping products or giving them to charity instead of making new purchases.
4. Users learn about their environmental impact while the system promotes them toward sustainable lifestyle choices.
5. Through registered locations including shelters and recycling hubs users can safely organize meetings for exchange transactions and donation drop-offs.
6. Users can browse through products composed of recycled materials and sustainable second-hand items and eco-friendly items for sale.
7. Users can access information about sustainable consumption through this section which also teaches upcycling methods and climate action practices.
8. The system raises public understanding while helping people keep sustainable actions long term.

